1. Prepare file.yaml
2. From GitLab reate a new project, create registry (left corner)
3. Run docker associated with the registry on the folder with the Dockerfile of interest
e.g.    $ cd pymc3
	$ docker build -t registry.ardigen.com/giovanni.mazzocco/gio_data_analysis .

4. Push the project on gitlab
	$ docker push registry.ardigen.com/giovanni.mazzocco/gio_data_analysis

5. Edit the image adress on the file.yaml

6. run kubernetes with the file.yaml
	e.g. $ kubectl create -f ppl_pod.yaml

7. Once the pod is created (e.g. pod/ppl-pod created) you can connect with the following command:
	$ kubectl exec -it ppl-pod /bin/bash


################ Here a list of useful commands:

List all pods in namespace 

     $ kubectl get pods
Create pods

     $ kubectl create -f pod.yaml
Describe your pod ( this is very usefull when something is wrong with your pod )

     $ kubectl describe pods podname   
Delete pod

     $ kubectl delete pods podname
Get into pod

     $ kubectl exec -it podname /bin/bash	
